<!DOCTYPE task PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Task//EN" "task.dtd">
<task id="task-7779" class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Seam Hole Repair</title><shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc "/><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><context class="- topic/section task/context ">Use this procedure when a seam has opened but the fabric is not missing.
</context><steps class="- topic/ol task/steps "><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Flip the item inside out.</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Align the fabric edges.</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Insert the needle slightly before the opening.
</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Sew along the original seam using a backstitch.
</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Continue until the opening is fully closed.
</cmd></step></steps><result class="- topic/section task/result ">The seam is securely repaired and matches the original stitching.
</result></taskbody></task>